Name: Dakar
Description: Dakar is the capital and largest city of Senegal and is often regarded as the cultural and commercial center of French-speaking West Africa. The metropolitan area is home to about 2.4 million people and lies on the end of the Cap Verte peninsula, which marks the westernmost point on the African mainland.

Name: Saint-Louis
Description: Saint-Louis is a city and a world heritage site on the Grande Cote in Northern Senegal.

Name: Thiès
Description: Thies (pronounced: "chess") (French:Thiès) is the capital of the Thies administrative region and the third largest city in Senegal.

Name: Kaolack
Description: Kaolack is a city in Senegal.

Name: Ziguinchor
Description: Ziguinchor is a city in the Casamance region of southern Senegal. The region is also referred to historically and popularly as Basse Casamance. Ziguinchor region is divided into 3 departments:

Name: Tambacounda
Description: Tambacounda is a city in the Tambacounda Region of southeastern Senegal. It is the main transport hub for Basse Casamance, Guinea and Mali.

Name: Kafountine
Description: Kafountine is a coastal village in the Casamance region of Senegal.

Name: Kedougou
Description: Kedougou is the capitol of the administrative region that bears its name. For purposes of this travel guide, it is considered part of the Tambacounda Region of southeastern Senegal.
